<HTML>
<Head>
<Title>Water Level Selection</Title>
</Head>
<Body>
<IMG SRC = "../figs/waver.gif">
<Br>
I'm looking for people interested in filling in part of my database for
Washington and California.  Specifically I would like for somebody to add the
guide book, page/run #, class, high/low flows, and drainage information.
This can be done with a text editor, a spreadsheet, or a database program.
If you are interested, please let me know!
<BR>
<A HRef=mailto:tpw@physics.orst.edu>Pat</A>
<Br>
<IMG SRC = "../figs/waver.gif">
<Br>
The water level information displayed here is collected from various sources.
For some of the flows I have estimated the actual flow by using other flow
information.  
<Br>
<B>
This information may not be correct, so please check the estimates!  
</B>
<Br>
If you have additional rivers, data sources, and/or inferred
levels, please <A HRef=mailto:tpw@physics.orst.edu>e-mail</A> with your 
suggestions.
<Br>
<Img Src=../figs/waver.gif>
